<item>
            <title>[LU-15274] loose reverse readahead</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15274</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some database queries end up going backwards through database files.&#160; This is most often in a &quot;loose backwards read&quot; manner similar to the &quot;loose forward reads&quot; described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15100&quot; title=&quot;Add ability to tune definition of loose sequential read&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15100&quot;&gt;LU-15100&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, reading backwards results in absolutely no readahead - every access is a miss.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ticket is to try to implement a simple &apos;loose backwards read&apos;.&#160; (Backwards strided readahead is a separate challenge and is left for another time.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
